    "v4 task model: test_objects declare mandatory test_types and transport_options.",
    "2.5D interposer topology: all dies at same z-height, connected via interposer metal layers.",
    "FPP per-die: only die0 and die2 have FPP lanes. die1 and die3 use serial TAP only.",
    "16 FPP lanes total connecting to die0 and die2 via interposer routing.",
    "Weaker vertical thermal coupling (no die stacking), but horizontal coupling applies between adjacent dies.",
    "Per-die BIST engines: BIST can run simultaneously across dies. Limited only by TAP config bandwidth and power.",
    "2.5D topology allows all dies to be accessed in parallel via FPP once configured -- but only dies with FPP hardware."
  ],
